KING CHARLES was within few late yeeres, quietly poſſeſt of three flouriſhing Kingdomes; and for a while, as his ſubjects ſeerned to enjoy all the blandiſhments of peace under his raigne, to the envie of other Nations; ſo hee appear'd eminently glorious in the inviolable loyalty and obedience of his ſubjects; 
   •
o the inciting of envie amongſt other Princes.
